# Studio Shed Component Specifications

This file provides detailed dimensional specifications for all components required to build the 10'×12' Signature Series Studio Shed in Blender.

## Precise Dimensions (Imperial to Metric)
```
1" = 0.0254m
1' = 0.3048m
```

## Foundation
- **Dimensions**: 12'0" × 10'0" × 6" (3.66m × 3.05m × 0.15m)
- **Material**: Concrete slab with vapor barrier
- **Modeling**: Single mesh with bevel on top edges

## Wall Panels (Main Types)

### Back Wall (7'3.5" height)
- **Full Panel**: 48" × 87.5" × 5.5" (1.22m × 2.22m × 0.14m)
- **Number Required**: 3 full panels
- **Interior Structure**: 2×4 studs at 16" O.C. with OSB sheathing

### Front Wall (8'6" height)
- **Full Panel**: 48" × 102" × 5.5" (1.22m × 2.59m × 0.14m)
- **Door Panel (Left/Right)**: 36" × 102" × 5.5" (0.91m × 2.59m × 0.14m)
- **Clerestory Window Panel**: 48" × 102" × 5.5" with window cutout
- **Number Required**: 1 full panel, 2 door panels, 1 window panel

### Side Walls (Sloped top edge)
- **Standard Panel**: 48" × variable height × 5.5" (1.22m × variable × 0.14m)
- **Window Panel**: 48" × variable height × 5.5" with 36"×36" window opening
- **Vistalite Panel**: 48" × variable height × 5.5" with full height window
- **Number Required**: 5 standard panels, 1 window panel, 1 vistalite panel

## Door Unit
- **Dimensions**: 72" × 80" × 1.75" (1.83m × 2.03m × 0.04m)
- **Material**: Glass panel with aluminum frame
- **Hardware**: Hinges on left side, handle on right
- **Detail**: Include aluminum trim around perimeter

## Window Units
- **Clerestory**: 36" × 18" (0.91m × 0.46m) along top of front wall
- **Standard Side**: 36" × 36" (0.91m × 0.91m)
- **Vistalite**: 24" × 84" (0.61m × 2.13m)
- **Construction**: Aluminum frames with glass panels
- **Operation**: Awning-style with appropriate hardware

## Roof Components

### Rafters
- **Dimensions**: 2" × 6" × appropriate length (0.05m × 0.15m × variable)
- **Spacing**: 24" on center (0.61m)
- **Overhang**: 24" front, 18" sides and back

### Roof Panels
- **Dimension**: Matching rafter spacing, full depth + overhangs
- **Structure**: 2×6 rafters with cross-blocking
- **Sections**: 2 outer sections, 4-5 intermediate sections

### Roofing Material
- **Type**: Corrugated metal panels
- **Dimension**: Standard 3' width panels (0.91m)
- **Overlap**: Minimum 6" side overlap, 12" at splices
- **Color**: Medium gray with slight texture

## Interior Components

### Drywall
- **Dimensions**: 4' × 8' × 1/2" (1.22m × 2.44m × 0.013m)
- **Layout**: Horizontal orientation
- **Finish**: Smooth, painted white

### Flooring
- **Material**: Engineered wood planks
- **Dimensions**: 48" × 7.5" × 3/4" (1.22m × 0.19m × 0.019m)
- **Pattern**: Running length of building

## Connection Hardware
- **A23 Brackets**: For rafter-to-top-plate connections
- **Teco Nails**: 1.5" length for brackets
- **Framing Nails**: 3" length for general framing
- **Roof Screws**: #12 × 3/4" with neoprene washers

## Specialty Items
- **Red-painted LVL Top Plates**: At specified locations
- **Zip Tape**: For sealing screw holes (except bottom window flange)
- **Shipping Blocks**: Removable pieces around windows
